# Post-Change Kernel Audit

After any code edit:

- MUST re-read the relevant loaded leaf pack(s) before judging the result; do not rely on memory.
- MUST inspect the actual diff against both `## KERNELS` and `## EXCLUDES` in the loaded leaves.
- MUST verify that every selected or claimed kernel is demonstrably satisfied by the diff, and that no exclusion pattern from the loaded leaves was introduced.
- MUST fix any mismatch immediately or report the violated entry by `pack/scope` and the exact trade-off explicitly.
- MUST keep the audit honest: if a loaded kernel was not materially relevant, omit it from the summary instead of citing it aspirationally.
